<br />        <a name=fax></a>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
          <tr>
          <td align="left" valign="center">
          <font size="+1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#F52E00>
          <b>Secure fax</b>
          </font>
          </td>
          </tr>
          <tr><td colspan=2 height=1><img src=../../../img/blank.gif width=1 height=1></td></tr>
          <tr><td height=4><img src="../../../img/blank.gif" width=1 height=4></td></tr>
        </table>
        <table width=100% border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
          <tr>
          <td valign=top align=left>
          <font size="-1" face="Lucida Grande,Arial,Verdana,sans-serif" color=#555555>
vIPer can be used to send secure fax messages, by connecting an external gateway
to the red dataport at the rear of the unit. The 90si Secure Fax Gateway shown
in the image on the right was approved for this application.
<br />
<br />
By adding a <a href="../../gwfs/90si/img/302873/000/full.jpg"><span data-balloon-pos="up" aria-label="More about: GFS-910 Fax Switcher">GFS-910 Fax Switcher</span></a>,
the same fax machine can also be used
for receiving non-secure fax messages, without swapping cables.
Both items were approved for use with vIPer.
